4. DELETE

1...deleteOne() deletes the first matching document. deleteMany() deletes all matching documents.

2...deleteMany({}) deletes all documents but keeps the collection itself. That's different from dropping the collection entirely.
Delete is irreversible — there's no built-in undo. Best practice is to run find() with the same condition first to confirm what will be deleted.

Example:
db.customers.deleteOne({ name: "Rahul" })
db.customers.deleteMany({ city: "Mumbai" })